latestPosts.caption:
Nobody told me this when I became a mom for the first time...

All I heard was:
❌ “Life khatam ho jaayegi ab.”
❌ “Ab toh sirf diapers aur neend ki kami hai.”
❌ “Apna time gaya.”
❌ “Shaadi ke baad toh change aata hi hai, ab mummy ban gayi ho...”
❌ “Ready rehna... pura din kaam hi kaam.”

But nobody told me the good part.
Nobody told me...

✅ That it’s still my life.
✅ That I can be a mother and still be me.
✅ That I get to decide what kind of mom I want to be.
✅ That I can wear kajal, chase dreams, take breaks — and still be a good mom.
✅ That motherhood is not about losing yourself… it’s about finding a stronger, softer, more powerful version of you.

People will always scare you with their rules.
But motherhood doesn’t come with one manual.
It’s all on you — how you want to live it.

💛 Some moms cook 5 meals a day.
💛 Some moms order food and cuddle.
💛 Some moms wear saris, some wear sweatpants.
💛 Some moms work outside, some work from home, some just want rest — and that’s okay.

Because there’s no “perfect” way.
Only your way.
And that’s always enough. 🌸

So no — my life didn’t end when I became a mom.
It started again — in the most beautiful, messy, magical way.
And I wouldn’t change a thing. ✨
